Kisumu county commissioner Mohammed Maalim has ordered a crackdown on illegal tuition in schools.He said the government has outlawed remedial classes and anybody found breaching the directive will be dealt with.Maalim said children must be given ample time to rest during the holidays.The commissioner yesterday directed the subcounty security team and chiefs to enforce the government ban on tuition. Maalim said the government will not tolerate lawlessness and action will be taken against officers who do not enforce the ban.The directive follows the arrest of 21 teachers for conducting tuition.Twelve teachers, including deputy head teacher Fredrick Owago, were arrested at Ahero Primary School in Nyando subcounty over illegal tuition on Monday. Education PS Belio Kipsang interdicted Owago for allowing remedial lessons in school.